The loop is a while loop that continues as long as the stack has at least two elements. Wait, the code in Java:

while (s.size() >1) {

   p = pop, q = pop. if pair → c++, continue (so loop again)

   else → push back and break.

} Wait, in the Java code, after popping p and q, if they form a pair, then the code increments c and continues the loop (so the next iteration of the while loop will check the new top elements).
